body_html:
For anyone wondering where the --default_ranges_min=0 and --default_ranges_max=6 values come from, see this note about dummy quantization, from the TOCO Command Line Examples documentation.

As they describe there, I got pretty poor accuracy after quantizing a retrained float MobileNet (the retrained model from the TensorFlow for Poets codelab)

body:
For anyone wondering where the `--default_ranges_min=0` and `--default_ranges_max=6` values come from, see [this note](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/blob/master/tensorflow/contrib/lite/toco/g3doc/cmdline_examples.md#use-dummy-quantization-to-try-out-quantized-inference-on-a-float-graph-) about dummy quantization, from the TOCO Command Line Examples documentation.

As they describe there, I got pretty poor accuracy after quantizing a retrained float MobileNet (the retrained model from the TensorFlow for Poets codelab)
